com.week5.util

Class List

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.week5.util.List

  • public class List
extends java.lang.Object
    A simple linked list. One may go through this list by advance() until the last position (endpos()) is reached. One also may delete() and add(Object) elements. After advancing it is possible to go back to the beginning by reset().

      • empty

        public boolean empty()
        Determines if this List is empty or not.
        Returns:
        true, if there are no elements in this List

      • endpos

        public boolean endpos()
        Determines if it is possible to advance() in this List. Returns true if the last position of this List has been reached. An empty() List will alway deliver true
        Returns:
        true if the last Entry in this List already has been reached.

      • reset

        Returns to the beginning of this List.

      • add

        public void add(java.lang.Object x)
        Inserts o in this List. It will be placed before the actual element. After insertion the inserted element will become the actual element.
        Parameters:
        x - the element to be inserted

      • delete

        public void delete()
        Deletes the actual element of this List. The element after the actual element will become the new actual element.
        Throws:
        RuntimeExcpetion - if the last Entry of this List already has been reached.
